hopobject.body: I'm a housewife clomiphene citrate yahoo answers In the decades following his death, the most powerful member states have often made it clear that they cannot tolerate the idea of a secretary-general acting with firmness or independence when it is against their perceived interests. The memoirs of Hammarskjold’s successors, such as Boutros Boutros-Ghali, illustrate this point. The article of the UN Charter that seems most systematically flouted is number 100, whereby member states undertake “not to seek to influence” the Secretariat staff in the conduct of their duties.
